eu.smartdatalake.simsearch.engine.processor.ingested

Class CategoricalSimSearch<K extends Comparable<? super K>,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.smartdatalake.simsearch.engine.processor.ingested.CategoricalSimSearch<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - Type variable representing the keys of the indexed objects.
    V - Type variable representing the values (sets of tokens) of the indexed objects.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISimSearch<K,V>

    public class CategoricalSimSearch<K extends Comparable<? super K>,V>
extends Object
implements ISimSearch<K,V>
    Implements kNN similarity search against a collection of sets of tokens indexed by an inverted index. Processing logic is similar to the one in All Pairs algorithm for set similarity joins

      • compute

        public int compute(IntSetCollection queryCollection,
                   IntSetCollection targetCollection,
                   Map<?,?> origTokenSetCollection,
                   int topk,
                   int M,
                   RankedList partialResults)
        Progressively collects the top-k most similar results. Once the score of a result is above the estimated score of any unseen items, this result is issued.
        Parameters:
        queryCollection - The (transformed) collection of tokens specified by the query.
        targetCollection - The (transformed) collection of the sets of tokens in the dataset.
        origTokenSetCollection - The original collection of the sets of tokens in the dataset.
        topk - The number of the final top-k results.
        M - The number of top-scoring results to fetch and populate the ranked list.
        partialResults - Queue to collect query results.
        Returns:
        The number of collected results.

        Returns the similarity score between two sets of tokens used in the verification stage of similarity search.
        Parameters:
        r - Array of datasetIdentifiers for the first set.
        s - Array of datasetIdentifiers for the second set.
        Returns:
        The Jaccard similarity between the two input sets.
